<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="sect sect-tinted" style="background:#ffffff;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="sect-head">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-wrap">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">Can Webority&rsquo;s platforms be deployed on NIC Data Centres and MeghRaj GI Cloud?</button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>Yes &mdash; we deploy on NIC Data Centres and MeghRaj GI Cloud, alongside empanelled sovereign and hyperscaler clouds. The topology is tailored to the data classification and the issuing department&rsquo;s cloud policy.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">Does Webority&rsquo;s e-governance software comply with GIGW 3.0 and WCAG 2.1 AA?</button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>We design against GIGW 3.0 and WCAG 2.1 AA from the first sprint, not as a remediation exercise. Conformance is verified through internal review and, where required, an independent audit before go-live.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">How does Webority handle Aadhaar, DigiLocker and UPI integration in government platforms?</button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>We work with the published India Stack APIs under the relevant arrangements (AUA / KUA for Aadhaar, DigiLocker partner credentials, NPCI / acquiring-bank arrangements for UPI). All integrations follow MeitY security guidelines and are reviewed for data-minimisation before go-live.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">Does Webority handle DPDP Act 2023 compliance for government data?</button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>Yes &mdash; our delivery applies data classification at design time, encrypts at rest and in transit, restricts access by role with audit logging, and aligns processing with the Digital Personal Data Protection Act 2023.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">Does Webority provide multi-vendor and multi-platform interoperability?</button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>We build on open standards and integrate with India Stack components and departmental ERPs &mdash; without locking the buyer into proprietary middleware or single-vendor licensing.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
